  "texts": [
    "• Retraining-Based Methods: Measure the training data's influence by repeatedly retraining model f using different subsets of training set D. • Gradient-Based Influence Estimators: Estimate influence via the alignment of training and test instance gradients either throughout or at the end of training.",
    "An in-depth comparison of these influence analysis methods requires detailed analysis so we defer the extensive discussion of these two categories to Sects.",
    "4 and 5, respectively.",
    "Table 1 summarizes the key properties of Fig. 2 's seven methods-including comparing each method's assumptions (if any), strengths/weaknesses, and asymptotic complexities.",
    "These three criteria are also discussed when detailing each of these methods in the later sections."
  ]
